      "content": "got it. so if i'm in the debate and my opponent brings up the systemic harm and racism, how do i pivot back to a \"logical\" defense? like, how can i argue that the \"stability\" side was actually the more responsible or \"realistic\" approach for a government or a bank to take to prevent a total economic collapse? basically, how do you frame the argument that these social distinctions were just a pragmatic necessity for economic survival?",
